cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CC, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of interactive cognitive assessment tools for healthcare systems, which involves the interaction between humans (doctors, therapists, patients) and computers.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper describes a semi-automatic approach to dementia assessment, which may involve the use of AI techniques.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the potential benefits of using digital tools for healthcare, which has societal implications.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve some computational complexity in the development of the digital pens and assessment tools.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also less likely but possible as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques in the assessment of dementia.
